In article <1992Sep27.073429.5833@muddcs.claremont.edu> ebrandt@jarthur.claremont.edu (Eli Brandt) writes:
>could provide the following feature:  if I finger the bogus user
>"callback:ebrandt" at a remote site, it will finger the user
>ebrandt@<my IP> and pass me the result.  This would require the

 Most fingers already do this - finger user@site1@site2  passes the
parameter user@site1 to site2.  In fact, if you're being silly, you
can put lots of hops in there.  (Occassionally you get a broken finger
that uses strchr(argv[1], '@') instead of strrchr :-) )

